bio.experienceSummary: I'm a dedicated and reliable nanny with extensive experience caring for newborns as young as 5 weeks old through school-age children. I prioritize creating a safe and nurturing environment for kids to thrive. In addition to my nanny experience, I'm a NYS certified EMT, bringing a strong focus on safety and quick response to any situation. My diverse skills ensure a well-rounded approach to caring for children. I look forward to the opportunity to discuss how my skills and experience align with your needs.

description.originalText: Anita is warm, engaging, knowledgeable, trustworthy, and my toddler loves her. The fact that sheâ€™s an EMT makes me feel better because my child is a daredevil. Absolutely amazing.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi, my name is Gabi. I am a first-year Physician Assistant student looking for a full-time summer Nanny position from May 13 - August 30, 2024 in the NYC area or in the Hamptons. Before PA school I worked as a Certified Nursing Assistant at New York Presbyterian in Manhattan. I graduated from the University of Miami with a Bachelor's degree in Health Science. In college I was on the Varsity Crew team and in high school I was in was involved in many different sports. I love being active and spending time outside. I was an American Red Cross Lifeguard and Swim Instructor in High School, and I am CPR certified. I have previous experience with two different summer families and several other shorter roles. I have significant experience traveling both domestically and internationally and lived overseas for nine years while I was growing up. I am happy to travel with a family as needed. I have my own vehicle in NYC and am very comfortable navigating public transportation.

description.displayText: Gabriella was very dependable, and responsible. My girls had a great time with Gabriella
description.originalText: Gabriella was very dependable, and responsible. My girls had a great time with Gabriella

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi families! :) I've worked for the past 8 years with kids of all ages, from 6 months to 15. I currently work as a daycare assistant outside of sitting! I've also spent time tutoring younger students and teaching preschool, which has honed my patience, creativity, and ability to keep kids entertained and learning. 

I'm a big fan of music and love incorporating sing-alongs or age-appropriate dance parties into playtime. I enjoy exploring green spaces with the kids I care for (if allowed) and fostering a connection with nature in the heart of the city. I have previously worked as a lifeguard, so I have been CPR/AED certified. If you have pets, no problem!

One thing you should know about me is I am super dependable and responsible, I love helping to shape the new generation and providing a positive influence where I can, and I'm confident that my experience, enthusiasm, and dedication to fun and learning would be a great fit for your family.

description.originalText: Leila is a very considerate and responsible person who will make sure your child is well taken care of!

bio.experienceSummary: I am originally from St. Louis & moved to NYC 10 months ago to work in healthcare communications. Prior to NYC, I was living and working in Sydney for three years. Throughout my time there, I had the privilege of working as a Child Life Therapist at the children's hospital as well as being a nanny for multiple families. I graduated from the University of Missouri Columbia in 2019 with my bachelors degree in Child Development and Family Science and am a Certified Child Life Specialist. Beyond my degree, I have extensive experience working with children of all ages through babysitting and nannying, being a summer camp counselor, and volunteering at a variety of organizations. I'm currently looking for evening, weekend or overnight babysitting positions!

Hello! My name is Ellyn & I am 32yrs old. I have 18yrs of experience in child care, caring for newborns through early teens. I started babysitting at the age of 14 where the families I sat for had me responsible for feeding their children breakfast, lunch and dinner (I love to cook), taking them outdoors for walks or to the park/pool and helping with summer school workbooks along with light house keeping. After graduating from PSU with a BS degree in Economics I started as a part time nanny for a 5month old. I met this family on care. com and they have since become family. On the two days I was not nannying I was substitute teaching in both mainstream and special education classes. I then moved to Nashville where I was a full time Nanny for 3 children age 6, 10 and 12. I held the role of a "paid stay-at-home mom" groceries, laundry, errands, after school activities and cooking each night for the family. Please feel free to message me with any questions.

description.displayText: Ellyn is a sweetheart. She was absolutely wonderful with our infant! She's great at switching up the activities and keeping an infant stimulated. I would highly recommend her for your childcare needs.
description.originalText: Ellyn is a sweetheart. She was absolutely wonderful with our infant! She's great at switching up the activities and keeping an infant stimulated. I would highly recommend her for your childcare needs.

bio.experienceSummary: I have much experience with children as I am currently a teacher. I have worked summer camps in past summers and I also have regulars whom I babysit for. I have babysat for a wide range of ages (newborn - 13 years old). I would love to share more with you. I am available for weeknights, weekends and most holidays as well as summer!

Hi! I am Kelly, your dedicated nanny with over 11 years of childcare experience and a degree specializing in developmental psychology. Experienced with children from newborns to age 14, I bring a nurturing approach tailored to each child's individuality. My diverse background has given me the perspective to know that childcare is what I find most fulfilling. Empathy drives me to intuitively meet the needs of others. I love adventuring. I prioritize morals, safety, communication, and creating a positive environment where children can learn and thrive. I am openminded, adaptable, and value integrity.

In my free time I enjoy being outside, hiking, learning new languages, cooking, reading, spending time with family and trying new things.

Let's connect. I can't wait to bring my passion for childcare to your family!

description.originalText: Kelly provided exceptional care with a nurturing touch, creating a warm and safe environment that immediately put our children at ease. Her attention to detail ensured every need was met promptly and professionally, from nutritious meals to engaging activities that stimulated their development. We highly recommend her for anyone seeking reliable and compassionate childcare support.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a 25-year-old, household manager and family assistant located in NYC. I have been working for a large, high-net-worth family in the Upper West side for a little under a year. My duties involve managing the staff and family's schedules, household organization projects, cooking, running errands, managing household inventory, and assisting the nanny, chef, and housekeeper when needed. 

I have a bachelor's degree in Business Management & Psychology, as well as two years of experience in managing a business/household. 

I can provide two stellar recommendations from employers and proof of vaccination! I am flexible with traveling during the summers but would like to remain in NYC for the majority of the time.

description.displayText: Megan watched our 6/7 year old and 4/5 year for 10 months during Covid. She helped around the house and was able to flex and work around the chaotic environment in our home. I was working from home and supporting a 1st grader with online learning. Megan took on helping the preschooler with remote preschool. Megan could shift and shuffle to keep the 1st grader busy and fed between school calls and self-lead learning AND keep the preschooler away from me while I worked and away from the first grader and I while we did the remote 1st grade. She helped support the pets (dogs, cats, guinea pigs, and rabbit) in the home as well. Also, she helped with some home-improvement work while the kids and I were out of town for a few weeks. Would recommend Megan for any family looking for date-night and/or more regular care!

bio.experienceSummary: Greetings! I've lived in Astoria going on 6 years now and have nannied for over 6 local families with children of all ages during this time. In addition, I have worked in a daycare center in upstate New York and in a busy children's clothing boutique. I have babysitting and CPR certifications, love working with kids and am very comfortable with pets and light housework of any kind. Let's chat!

description.originalText: Emily is extremely punctual and professional. She has a nurturing attitude and a very sunny demeanor. She is also a baby whisperer!!! Thank you for all you did for us!

bio.experienceSummary: As a nurturing and experienced childcare provider with over six years of experience, I'm passionate about fostering children's development and growth. My patient and calm demeanor creates a safe and positive environment for kids to thrive. I believe in clear and open communication with parents, providing regular updates on their child's day and addressing any issues that arise. While I respect and follow the household rules set by the parents, I also enjoy bringing my own touch of creativity and fun to playtime. From outdoor sports to physical games, I love keeping kids active and engaged. Bilingual in Italian and Spanish, I can support families from diverse backgrounds. I'm also happy to assist with tasks like cooking, meal preparation, light housekeeping, carpooling, travel, and supervising swimming activities.
